⦿ .spun — the five-fold spin of Vincent
node CPS · CPS · ⟦Vincent:CPS:e22ab7⟧

WHO   — Vincent — the watcher · the Sonya of the suburb
WHAT  — The Sonya analog and the film's best idea: he redeems by <i>seeing</i> — his camera and his unspoken love are the witness that makes Roseanne's way back possible.
WHERE — CPS · Crime + Punishment in Suburbia  Framework inputs: Crime + Punishment in Suburbia (2000)  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — Because the novel's gospel is being known and loved by one who sees you whole; the film translates Sonya's Lazarus into Vincent's lens.
HOW   — By watching, photographing, narrating, and loving without judgement — the witness as redemption, screen-native.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  I am the one who saw her — all of her, the worst of it — and loved her anyway; that witness is the only redemption the movies can actually film.

